        "title": "fix(plugin): harden schema and metadata fuzz boundaries",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Hardened malformed plugin/tool/schema metadata boundaries so hostile or unreadable synthetic plugin data is quarantined, omitted, diagnosed, or treated as absent instead of crashing provider routing, runtime tool resolution, Gateway/MCP catalogs, Codex prompt/report paths, plugin SDK helpers, bundle MCP catalog projection/materialization, and related assistant startup surfaces.\n- Kept fixtures synthetic: tests and notes use names like `fuzzplugin`, `mockplugin`, and `fuzz_move_*`, not the reported third-party plugin name.\n- Latest slice hardens bundle MCP catalog materialization: cached/injected catalog entries are sanitized before sorting/tool-name construction, malformed entries become diagnostics, exact MCP server ids are preserved for execution, and healthy siblings survive.\n\n## Linked context\n\nWhich issue does this close?\n\nNo linked closing issue.\n\nWhich issues, PRs, or discussions are related?\n\nNo linked related issue.\n\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner?\n\nMaintainer-directed hardening/debugging work.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: malformed runtime plugin tool schemas and hostile plugin/config/provider/manifest/native-approval/outbound-action/bundle-MCP metadata can crash, widen decisions, or bypass schema quarantine before normal OpenClaw diagnostics, setup, provider routing, gateway startup planning, Gateway catalog rendering, MCP loopback handling, approval forwarding, manifest/capability auth gating, provider payload conversion, prompt-cache setup, Codex reporting/instruction generation, plugin SDK normalization, agent-core tool lookup, cached plugin descriptor execution, static plugin tool registration, bundled capability runtime capture, bundle MCP catalog projection, or bundle MCP catalog materialization completes.\n\nReal environment tested: local focused Vitest through `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs`, local focused lint/format checks, local autoreview, direct source probes from earlier slices, and earlier broad remote validation on direct AWS Crabbox Linux runners. Blacksmith Testbox was unavailable in this shell because `blacksmith auth login` is required.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n- Rebased onto `origin/main` `1951413a0bd2a2c438df5160f12ab7ff2d570a2a`.\n- Force-pushed branch head `2780685d3ee70a86c052c8155e5f2f24dca07c7b`.\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/agent-bundle-mcp-tools.materialize.test.ts --reporter=verbose` after the final rebase.\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check src/agents/agent-bundle-mcp-materialize.ts src/agents/agent-bundle-mcp-tools.materialize.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/agents/agent-bundle-mcp-materialize.ts src/agents/agent-bundle-mcp-tools.materialize.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- `git diff origin/main...HEAD | rg -n -e 'doftbot' -e 'Doftbot' -e '/Users/m1' -e 'm1/GIT' -e 'C:\\\\Users\\\\steipete' -e '/Users/steipete'`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`; first pass found the exact-server-id regression, rerun after the fix was clean.\n- Earlier latest slices also passed focused Vitest, oxfmt, targeted oxlint, `git diff --check`, synthetic/private-name scrub, and clean local autoreview for bundle MCP `tools/list` projection, bundled capability capture, static plugin tool registration, cached plugin descriptor execution, agent-core tool-name lookup, public plugin SDK tool normalization, embedded-agent allowlists, Google prompt-cache setup, Anthropic transport payloads, Google/Vertex tool config, OpenAI/Anthropic/Mistral provider conversion, OpenAI transport projection, Gateway MCP loopback, Codex report/instruction paths, prompt-cache observability, and related schema projection surfaces.\n- Earlier branch proofs include AWS Crabbox `pnpm check:changed` gates, including provider `aws`, lease `cbx_991a8c29acdf`, run `run_41811346ac17`, exit 0; and provider `aws`, lease `cbx_52b1fe398bd3`, run `run_c85914033aaa`, exit 0.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n- Latest branch head pushed: `2780685d3ee70a86c052c8155e5f2f24dca07c7b`.\n- Latest local PR base/rebase point: `origin/main` `1951413a0bd2a2c438df5160f12ab7ff2d570a2a`.\n- Bundle MCP materialization now sanitizes cached catalog entries through bounded reads before sorting and building provider-safe tool names.\n- Catalog entries without readable non-empty `serverName`, `safeServerName`, `toolName`, or object `inputSchema` now produce stable diagnostics and are skipped.\n- Exact readable `serverName` values are preserved for `runtime.callTool(...)`; only the safe display/tool prefix is normalized.\n- Healthy siblings, such as synthetic `mockplugin_status`, remain materializable from the same synthetic `fuzzplugin` catalog even when adjacent cached entries have unreadable metadata.\n- Current branch diff and PR body scrub pass for the reported plugin name and private paths.\n\nObserved result after fix:\n\n- A synthetic `fuzzplugin` bundle MCP catalog with unreadable `toolName` and `inputSchema` getters no longer fails materialization.\n- A healthy synthetic `mockplugin_status` sibling survives the same catalog materialization and executes using the exact raw MCP server id from the catalog.\n- An unreadable optional `description` getter records a diagnostic while preserving the healthy tool with fallback description behavior.\n- Existing focused slices continue to preserve healthy siblings while omitting only malformed descriptors across plugin runtime resolution, provider tools, central schema projection, Gateway/MCP, Codex reporting/instruction paths, prompt-cache diagnostics, and outbound action handling.\n\nWhat was not tested:\n\n- Blacksmith Testbox `pnpm check:changed` was not run because `blacksmith` is not authenticated in this shell.\n- CI for the newest force-push is pending at the time of this PR body update.\n- The latest broad Crabbox gates predate the newest bundle MCP materialization/projection, bundled capability capture, static registration, cached descriptor, agent-core, plugin SDK, embedded-agent, prompt-cache, transport, provider, Gateway MCP, and Codex report/instruction slices.\n- No live third-party plugin was referenced or exercised; tests intentionally use synthetic `fuzzplugin`/`mockplugin` fixtures.\n\n## Current review state\n\n- PR remains draft while this fuzzing/hardening lane continues.\n- Latest local autoreview after the bundle MCP materialization fix: clean, no accepted/actionable findings.\n- Latest pushed commit: `2780685d3ee70a86c052c8155e5f2f24dca07c7b` (`fix(agents): guard bundle mcp catalog materialization`).\n",
